reviews.review: I ignored the negative reviews, went to go see it for myself. I thought it was a great movie it was fun and really tied up a lot of loose ends I definitely recommend you watch it and dont let critics sway you.

The rating is all for the visuals and the actors - as for story, logic and Star Wars lore, including an objectively good movie - it should be a minus 2 mentioned in the same sentance as The Room. It's insanely stupid with plot-holes the size of galaxies, it's filled with agenda even if less than Last Jedi, and it's just a lousy movie that is stupid beyond imagination. It also means the end of Star Wars caring for me - it's finally dead and dusted burned to a cinder by Disney.

I was born in the mid 70's and have grown up with this saga.  As a person who has been immersed in this universe almost from birth, I was very happy with this movie and how it concluded the saga.  Was it the perfect movie? No, but I don't go enjoy these films looking for perfection or my personal fan fiction to be made into reality.  I go to be told a story and I absolutely enjoyed it.   I'll definitely be going back to see it again.

This movie ruined most of the things that I LOVED about Star Wars. Anakin's story is pointless now, the pacing of the movie was super fast paced. It felt like 2 movies crammed into one. The plot doesn't make any sense. If you are a casual movie goer that doesn't care about lore then this is a decent movie. But if you LOVE Star Wars lore then you'll probably hate this as much as I do.
